  "prompt": "How many grafts are needed to get a full beard by facial hair transplant? How much will it cost in India?",
  "response": "The number of grafts required for a full beard transplant can vary significantly based on the individual\u2019s existing facial hair, the desired beard thickness, and the areas to be covered. On average, a full beard transplant may require anywhere from 2,500 to 3,000 grafts. However, for partial coverage or to fill in patchy areas, fewer grafts might be needed.\n\nThe cost of a beard transplant in India can also vary depending on the clinic's location, its reputation, the surgeon's experience, and the complexity of the procedure. Generally, the cost can range from \u20b930 to \u20b9100 per graft. This means a full beard transplant could cost anywhere from \u20b975,000 to \u20b9300,000 or more.\n\nIt's important to have a consultation with a qualified specialist who can provide a more accurate assessment based on your specific needs and circumstances.",
